Lionel Messi's Argentina geared up for their international showdown with Portugal at Old Trafford on Tuesday by training at Manchester City's Carrington headquarters.

The Barcelona superstar and his international team-mates his the training pitch in Manchester to continue their preparations for their game against Cristiano Ronaldo's Portugal.

Manchester City's own Sergio Aguero and Martin Demichelis were also present for the session at their club's training complex. 

